        "subject": "LU-2523 mdt: handle -ENOENT && !MDS_OPEN_CREAT in reint open",
        "message": "LU-2523 mdt: handle -ENOENT && !MDS_OPEN_CREAT in reint open\n\nIf mdt_open_anon_by_fid() returns -ENOENT and MDS_OPEN_CREAT is not\nset in create flags then bail out and return -ENOENT from\nmdt_reint_open().  In mdt_open_anon_by_fid() if -ENOENT is returned\nthen ensure that DISP_IT_EXECD is set in the reply disposition.  Add\nsanity test_27B to call the LL_IOC_LOV_SETSTRIPE ioctl() on an open\nunlinked file, a situation which triggers the first case.  In sanityn\ntest 30, remote the requirement that opening an unlinked file via\n/proc/PID/exe return -ESTALE.\n\nLustre-commit: dfe7fcd415fa40e2ab059c5201f7df4e2e174e54\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/5417\n\nIntel-bug-id: LU-3311\nSigned-off-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Jinshan Xiong <jinshan.xiong@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <james.a.nunez@intel.com>\nChange-Id: If81b3cc7f59eb9760c00835cdc3e0eb64d0ac94f\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
